<subSubSection id="4F9065400605091DFF31FBB6FA55FAC6" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="073536CB0605091DFF31FBB6FA55FAC6" blockId="16.[151,1437,1117,2006]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFF31FBB6FECDFBB6" bold="true" box="[151,273,1117,1142]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Prostomium pointed, conical; peristomium typically with one achaetous ring, but with additional superficial annulae on some species. Branchiae lacking, or present from posterior thoracic, transitional, or abdominal setiger. Posterior thoracic setigers with 0–2 postsetal lobes and 0–2 subpodial lobes; abdominal setigers with 0–4 subpodial papillae; stomach papillae rare, interramal cirri present or absent. Thoracic neurosetae including only capillaries. Without abdominal neuropodial spines, with 2–3 imbedded aciculae present or absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4F9065400605091CFF61FAFAFC2AFF70" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="18" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="073536CB0605091DFF61FAFAFEF9F9E6" blockId="16.[151,1437,1117,2006]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<materialsCitation id="B7E23C960605091DFF61FAFAFB67FAB1" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424727821" country="New Zealand" location="NZ" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFF61FAFAFEE7FAEA" bold="true" box="[199,315,1297,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="631B4B3A0605091DFEE1FAF9FE11FAEA" author="Day" box="[327,461,1298,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Day, J. H. (1977) A review of the Australian and New Zealand Orbiniidae (Annelida: Polychaeta). In: Reish, D. J. &amp; Fauchald, K. (Eds.), Essays on Polychaetous Annelids in Memory of Dr. Olga Hartman, pp. 217 - 246. [Allan Hancock Foundation, University of Southern California, Los Angeles.]" type="book chapter" year="1977">Day (1977)</bibRefCitation>
determined that the 
<typeStatus id="D83188690605091DFD6CFAF9FD26FAEA" box="[714,762,1298,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFC21FAFAFB34FAEA" authority="Monro, 1933a" authorityName="Monro" authorityYear="1933" box="[903,1256,1297,1322]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Haploscoloplos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orbiniida" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFC21FAFAFBEBFAE9" box="[903,1079,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Haploscoloplos</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="631B4B3A0605091DFBE2FAF9FB34FAEA" author="Monro" box="[1092,1256,1298,1322]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Monro, C. C. A. (1933 a) On a collection of Polychaeta from Dry Tortugas, Florida. Annals &amp;. Magazine of Natural History, London, series 10, vol. 12, 244 - 269." type="journal article" year="1933" yearSuffix="a">Monro, 1933a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFB58FAF9FE9EFA8E" authority="Ehlers, 1904" authorityName="Ehlers" authorityYear="1904" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Haploscoloplos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polychaeta incertae sedis" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cylindrifer">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFB58FAF9FA40FAE9" box="[1278,1436,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">H. cylindrifer</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="631B4B3A0605091DFF31FADEFE9EFA8E" author="Ehlers" box="[151,322,1333,1358]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Ehlers, E. (1904) Neuseelandische Anneliden. Abhhandlungen der koniglichen Gesellschaft der Wissenschaften zu Gottingen, Mathematisch-Physikalische Klasse, Neue Folge 3, 1 - 80, plates 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1904">(Ehlers, 1904))</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
possessed an anterior row of short hooks in the thoracic neuropodia in addition to capillaries and thus belonged to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFE75FAB2FD9CFAB1" box="[467,576,1369,1393]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Scoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFE75FAB2FD9CFAB1" box="[467,576,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Scoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He examined a specimen from near Christchurch, 
<collectingCountry id="7F9D765B0605091DFB34FAB1FB67FAB1" box="[1170,1211,1370,1393]" name="New Zealand" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">NZ</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
; 
<materialsCitation id="B7E23C960605091DFB6EFAB2FEF9F9E6" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1424727830" country="New Zealand" location="South Island" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<location id="025560100605091DFB6EFAB2FA86FAB2" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:8F2387DD0605091CFF31FC3FFC2AFF70:025560100605091DFB6EFAB2FA86FAB2" box="[1224,1370,1369,1394]" country="New Zealand" name="South Island" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">South Island</location>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7F9D765B0605091DFAC1FAB1FF28FA56" name="New Zealand" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, near the 
<typeStatus id="D83188690605091DFEC4FA95FE4EFA56" box="[354,402,1406,1430]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality of the species. He therefore proposed a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFB98FA96FB3DFA55" box="[1086,1249,1405,1429]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFB98FA96FB3DFA55" box="[1086,1249,1405,1429]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Leitoscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to include those remaining species formerly assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFDD0FA4AFCFAFA79" authority="" authorityName="" box="[630,806,1441,1465]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Haploscoloplos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polychaeta incertae sedis" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFDD0FA4AFCFAFA79" box="[630,806,1441,1465]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Haploscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Most of the known species of 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFB12FA4AFA8BFA79" box="[1204,1367,1441,1465]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFB12FA4AFA8BFA79" box="[1204,1367,1441,1465]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Leitoscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were summarized by 
<bibRefCitation id="631B4B3A0605091DFEEBFA2EFE24FA1E" author="Mackie" box="[333,504,1477,1502]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Mackie, A. S. Y. (1987) A review of the species currently assigned to the genus Leitoscoloplos Day, 1977 (Polychaeta: Orbiniidae), with descriptions of species newly referred to Scoloplos Blainville, 1828. Sarsia, 72, 1 - 28, 24 figures." type="book chapter" year="1987">Mackie (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. Those species have been reconsidered as part of this study. Several new species, new combinations, and new synonymies are proposed from the materials examined as part of this study and are listed below.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="073536CB0605091DFF61F9D9FDB1F93D" blockId="16.[151,1437,1117,2006]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
An assessment of branchial distribution suggests that 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFCBAF9DAFC1CF989" box="[796,960,1585,1609]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFCBAF9DAFC1CF989" box="[796,960,1585,1609]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Leitoscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be divided into five groups of species. Geographically, species within these groups also have some affiliation to their distribution globally. For example, the two abranchiate species in Group A are deep-sea abyssal species; the three species in Group C occur only along the Atlantic and Gulf coasts of North America, and all 11 species in groups D and E occur in the southern hemisphere of which seven occur in the 
<collectingRegion id="C54EF8290605091DFDD2F92AFD05F91A" box="[628,729,1729,1754]" country="Sri Lanka" name="Southern" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Southern</collectingRegion>
Ocean. The 11 species in Group B are the most ubiquitous, occurring widely over the world’s oceans.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="073536CB0605091DFF61F8E2FD98F816" blockId="16.[151,1437,1117,2006]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This study suggests that previous records of certain widely recorded species need to be reevaluated. For example, the record of 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFE0CF8C6FD2CF885" authority="" authorityName="" box="[426,752,1837,1861]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Haploscoloplos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polychaeta incertae sedis" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kerguelensis">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFE0CF8C6FD2CF885" box="[426,752,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Haploscoloplos kerguelensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the eastern Mediterranean by 
<bibRefCitation id="631B4B3A0605091DFB3FF8C5FAE0F886" author="Ramos" box="[1177,1340,1837,1862]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Ramos, J. M. (1976), Haploscoloplos kerguelensis McIntosh, 1885 - nouvel Orbiniidae en Mediterranee occidentale. Vie et Milieu, 26 (1 A), 1 - 9, 2 figures." type="book chapter" year="1976">Ramos (1976)</bibRefCitation>
is most certainly an undescribed species (see Discussion of 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFC91F8B9FC31F8A9" authority="" authorityName="" box="[823,1005,1873,1897]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Haploscoloplos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polychaeta incertae sedis" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kerguelensis">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFC91F8B9FC31F8A9" box="[823,1005,1873,1897]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. kerguelensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below). Similar identifications of 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFF31F89EFE9BF84D" authority="" authorityName="" box="[151,327,1909,1933]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Haploscoloplos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polychaeta incertae sedis" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFF31F89EFE9BF84D" box="[151,327,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Haploscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFED8F89EFD61F84D" box="[382,701,1909,1933]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kerguelensis">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFED8F89EFD61F84D" box="[382,701,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Leitoscoloplos kerguelensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Asia also need to be reconsidered (see below). One undescribed deep-sea species of 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480605091DFDB7F872FD69F871" box="[529,693,1945,1969]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90605091DFDB7F872FD69F871" box="[529,693,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Leitoscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently identified from offshore 
<collectingCountry id="7F9D765B0605091DFBD3F872FA93F872" box="[1141,1359,1945,1970]" name="Brunei" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Brunei Darussalam</collectingCountry>
in the South 
<collectingCountry id="7F9D765B0605091DFF79F856FEFEF816" box="[223,290,1981,2006]" name="China" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">China</collectingCountry>
Sea (Blake unpublished).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="073536CB0604091CFF31FF7CFC2AFF70" blockId="17.[151,1014,151,176]" box="[151,1014,151,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
According to this revision, 
<taxonomicName id="C08A4D480604091CFE6EFF73FDB0FF70" box="[456,620,152,176]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="35FEEAD90604091CFE6EFF73FDB0FF70" box="[456,620,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Leitoscoloplos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are categorized as follows:
</paragraph>
